The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Bengal Hockey Association (BHA) has come forward to help the legendary Leslie Claudius. The four-time Olympic gold winner has been recuperating from pneumonia at a city nursing home. According to nursing home sources, he is still in intensive care but his condition is stable.       
	BHA chief J.B. Roy flew into the city from New Delhi on Friday to hand over a cheque of Rs 1 lakh to Claudiuss family.       
	Roy, accompanied by secretary Gurbux Singh, also called on sports minister Subhas Chakraborty regarding the plot for laying astroturf.           
	 Manipur and Orissa eased their way into the semi-finals of the senior national womens football meet in Haldia on Friday.       
	According to information received here, Manipur, riding N. Baladevis four goals, thrashed Tripura 8-0 while Orissa accounted for Chhattisgarh 6-0 in the quarter finals. Tenkipurm Kar scored a hattrick for Orissa.       
	Bengal will take on Tamil Nadu on Saturday.                 
